And we may still end up with ridiculously overpriced games.

In conclusion. There are no solutions to this problem that are “good” for football. We either go back to stupidly expensive games, slaves building our stadiums for world cups and isolating fans or we move on, the clubs have more control, but the fans may get isolated again..:

This brings me on to Sky Sports. Jamie Carragher said it tonight. The hypocrisy that those pundits who work for sky calling the managers, players and clubs out for being greedy when they charged £15 for one game last season is unbelievably hypocritical.
Threatening to take UCL and UEL semi finals away from teams just because they stand up against the corrupt, money grabbing bodies the govern football is not okay.

But it’s not just these top clubs that are at fault here. UEFA and FIFA are blackmailing the top clubs in order to keep their power, they don’t care about the people in the game, or they would’ve made a bigger point against Racism in football. It’s all about money.
And 9th would be playing in the top competition, whilst Leicester and West Ham who would be looking forward to Champions League next year, are playing in the second most important competition.

Here’s where I begin to disagree with these clubs. If those 15 clubs want to run their own competition which they fund, they would never sign up unless they are guaranteed to play in it every year. Now the pyramid of football is ruined. Teams that currently sit 5th, 6th, 7th...

Over who broadcasts what and at what price point. This could mean fans all over the world would have access to all of their clubs games on one subscription service. The most logical way to knock UEFA off? Override their biggest moneymaker. The Champions League...

If UEFA and FIFA don’t? That’s where the super league comes into play. An organisation made up of the big clubs could easily fund all the big competitions in the world, they could prevent slaves building stadiums, the isolation of fans (Baku UEL final 2019) and have control...

UEFA, FIFA, the FA and the broadcasting companies have made terrible decisions without consequences over the last 20 years. There isn’t really a need for these organisations at all, the clubs can run it themselves but they need funding. Who’s gonna fund these competitions...
Right I have had a whole day to digest everything and here’s where I currently sit on everything that’s going on right now.
